Boil a large #pot{} of salted water.

Chop the @potatoes{600%g} into 2cm chunks.

Strip the leafy part of the @kale{80%g} from the stem. Tear into small pieces. Discard the stem.

Add the potatoes to the boiling water. Cook until fork tender, ~{12-18%minutes}. Add the kale in the final ~{2-3%minutes} of cooking time.

Drain in a #colander{}. Return to the pot, off the heat. Mash with a knob of @butter{} and a splash of @milk{} or @water{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cover to keep warm.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve, peel and chop the @shallot{1}(peeled and chopped) into small pieces.

Place your hand flat on top of the @Irish chicken breast{320%g} and slice through horizontally to make two thin steaks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal due to packaging we use to keep it fresh.

== Garlic Butter Sauce ==

Place a separate #pot{} over medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Once hot, fry the shallot until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add the garlic and cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Pour in half the @apple cider vinegar{1/2%sachet} and allow to evaporate.

Add @flour{1%tsp} to the pot and mix well to incorporate.

Stir in @water{100%ml} along with the @chicken stock{1%sachet} and bring to the boil.

Lower the heat and mix in @butter{1%tbsp}.

Simmer until the butter has melted and the sauce has thickened slightly, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Remove from the heat and cover to keep warm.

> TIP: If necessary, reheat the sauce just before serving.

== Cajun Chicken ==

Meanwhile, place a large pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Toss the chicken with @Cajun spice mix{1%sachet}, @salt{}, @pepper{} and a drizzle of @oil{}.

When the pan hot, add the chicken steaks and cook through, ~{3-6%minutes} each side.

> IMPORTANT: Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the @peas{120%g} to the pan for the final ~{2%minutes} of cooking time.

> TIP: Cook in batches if your pan is too crowded.

== To Serve ==

Thinly slice the chicken widthways.

Divide the colcannon between plates.

Serve the Cajun chicken and peas alongside.

Drizzle the garlic butter sauce over the chicken.